{"id":"1609.07226","submitter":"Brad Safnuk","authors":"Brad Safnuk","title":"Combinatorial models for moduli spaces of open Riemann surfaces","comments":"15 pages. Comments welcome!","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.SG math-ph math.GT math.MP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We present a simplified formulation of open intersection numbers, as an\nalternative to the theory initiated by Pandharipande, Solomon and Tessler. The\nrelevant moduli spaces consist of Riemann surfaces (either with or without\nboundary) with only interior marked points. These spaces have a combinatorial\ndescription using a generalization of ribbon graphs, with a straightforward\ncompactification and corresponding intersection theory. Crucially, the\ngenerating functions for the two different constructions of open intersection\nnumbers are identical. In particular, our construction provides a complete\nproof of the statement that this generating function is a solution of the MKP\nhierarchy, satisfies W-constraints, and additionally proves in the affirmative\nthe Q-grading conjecture for distinguishing contributions from surfaces with\ndifferent numbers of boundary components, as was previously proposed by the\nauthor.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 23 Sep 2016 04:15:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 29 Sep 2016 14:55:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-30"}
